<div id="paperContent">
  <h2>Skin Cancer Detection Using Machine Learning â€“ Research Paper Overview</h2>
  <p><strong>Objective:</strong> Develop a machine learning model for early detection of melanoma from dermoscopic images, aiding in faster diagnosis and treatment.</p>
  <p><strong>Technologies Used:</strong> Python, TensorFlow, Keras, CNNs, OpenCV, ISIC Dataset</p>
  <p><strong>Methodology:</strong> Images were preprocessed and classified using CNN. Techniques like data augmentation and dropout layers were applied to boost model performance and avoid overfitting.</p>
  <p><strong>Results:</strong> Achieved over 89% accuracy with strong metrics like F1-score and ROC-AUC. Model proved promising for medical image diagnostics.</p>
  <p><strong>Contributions:</strong> Developed a full pipeline, explored ethical considerations, and proposed future improvements including mobile integration.</p>
  <p><strong>What I Learned:</strong> Deepened my understanding of ML in healthcare, image processing, and deployment strategies.</p>
  <p><strong>Future Scope:</strong> Expand the model into a real-time mobile/web tool for early skin cancer risk detection in remote areas.</p>
